==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|soken}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|socian||to soak, steep|lit=to cause to suck (up)}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*sukōną||to soak}}, causative of {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*sūkaną||to suck}}. Cognate with {{cog|dum|soken||to cause to suck}}. More at {{l|en|suck}}.

